sudden? Well in large part because of better captions. But which better

00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:09.119
captions? The previous model used all the good captions. Well they synthesized

00:21:09.119 --> 00:21:13.000
the captions. That's how you get high quality data. Of course you have to do

00:21:13.040 --> 00:21:20.760
this with care, but there are many more piling examples of task-specific

00:21:20.760 --> 00:21:25.640
symbolic knowledge distillation, including the work of my own lab, that

00:21:25.640 --> 00:21:31.719
demonstrate that this could really make smaller models really unlock the hidden

00:21:31.719 --> 00:21:37.319
capabilities of small models. So it's really about quality, novelty, and

00:21:37.319 --> 00:21:41.400
diversity of your data, not just the quantity, and I'll end my talk here.

00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:43.880
Thank you.

00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:59.880
Awesome. Okay, so there we had it. Mission Impossible. So the secret sauce behind

00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:07.640
these SLMs, small language models, is the data. Surprise. Okay, awesome. So back to

00:22:07.640 --> 00:22:10.640
this slide. We saw it yesterday. So this is the Data Intelligence Platform, and

