So I have a somewhat longer session for you today,

00:45:25.771 --> 00:45:28.852
because I'm talking about governance

00:45:28.852 --> 00:45:32.131
with open source Unity Catalog, as well as data sharing.

00:45:32.131 --> 00:45:34.531
If you're familiar, we have another open source project.

00:45:34.531 --> 00:45:35.692
We launched delta sharing.

00:45:35.692 --> 00:45:39.812
That's really making waves in the open data collaboration

00:45:39.812 --> 00:45:43.572
space, and we have a lot of exciting announcements

00:45:43.572 --> 00:45:44.531
around that.

00:45:44.531 --> 00:45:47.852
So I'll start by talking about what's new in Unity Catalog

00:45:47.852 --> 00:45:49.972
and what it means to open source it, why we did it,

00:45:49.972 --> 00:45:51.171
what's in there.

00:45:51.171 --> 00:45:53.131
And then, so Ali announced that we're

00:45:53.131 --> 00:45:55.251
open sourcing it yesterday, but he

00:45:55.251 --> 00:45:57.732
let me keep one more thing to announce today

00:45:57.732 --> 00:45:58.891
that I'll talk about.

00:45:58.891 --> 00:46:02.251
That's the next big direction for Unity Catalog.

00:46:02.251 --> 00:46:04.092
And then, finally, I'll switch gears

00:46:04.092 --> 00:46:05.891
to sharing and collaboration, and we'll

00:46:05.891 --> 00:46:08.692
have some cool demos of all these things, too.

00:46:08.692 --> 00:46:11.031
So let's start with Unity Catalog.

00:46:11.031 --> 00:46:13.932
So I think everyone who works in data and AI

00:46:13.932 --> 00:46:18.671
knows that governance, whether it's for security or quality

00:46:18.671 --> 00:46:20.832
or compliance, remains a huge challenge

00:46:20.832 --> 00:46:22.651
for many applications.

00:46:22.651 --> 00:46:25.171
And it's getting even harder with generative AI.

00:46:25.171 --> 00:46:28.732
There are new regulations being written all the time about it.

00:46:28.732 --> 00:46:30.812
I heard in California alone, there

00:46:30.812 --> 00:46:35.171
are 80 bills proposed that regulate AI in some form.

00:46:35.171 --> 00:46:37.051
And also, you need to really understand

00:46:37.051 --> 00:46:38.972
where your data is coming from if you're

00:46:38.972 --> 00:46:41.171
going to create models and deploy them

00:46:41.171 --> 00:46:42.651
and run these applications.

00:46:42.651 --> 00:46:44.371
So we hear things from our customers

00:46:44.371 --> 00:46:46.612
all the time about how they would love to use AI,

00:46:46.612 --> 00:46:50.771
but they can't really govern it with their existing frameworks.

00:46:50.771 --> 00:46:53.251
And even on the data space, it's complex enough.

00:46:53.251 --> 00:46:55.651
Even there, all the rules are changing,

00:46:55.651 --> 00:46:58.812
and people are really worried about how to best do it.

00:46:58.812 --> 00:47:03.371
So we wanted to step back and think, it's 2024.

00:47:03.371 --> 00:47:05.612
If you had to design an ideal governance

00:47:05.612 --> 00:47:08.651
solution from scratch today, what would you want it to have?

00:47:08.651 --> 00:47:10.651
We asked a bunch of CIOs.

00:47:10.651 --> 00:47:13.771
And we thought you really wanted to have three things.

00:47:13.771 --> 00:47:16.452
The first thing is what we call open connectivity.

00:47:16.452 --> 00:47:19.771
So you should be able to take any data, any source that's

00:47:19.771 --> 00:47:23.051
in your organization, and plug it into the governance

00:47:23.051 --> 00:47:25.732
solution, because no one's going to migrate everything

00:47:25.732 --> 00:47:28.771
into just one data system over time.

00:47:28.771 --> 00:47:31.732
Most organizations have hundreds or thousands of these.

00:47:31.732 --> 00:47:33.432
So you really want a governance solution

00:47:33.432 --> 00:47:35.972
that can really cover all this data wherever

00:47:35.972 --> 00:47:41.092
it lives, in any format, even in other platforms.

00:47:41.092 --> 00:47:44.131
Then we also really think you need unified governance

00:47:44.131 --> 00:47:45.332
across data and AI.

00:47:45.332 --> 00:47:48.011
I think it's clearer than ever with generative AI

00:47:48.011 --> 00:47:49.891
that you have to manage these together.

00:47:49.891 --> 00:47:53.651
You can't be managing AI without knowing what data went into it.

00:47:53.651 --> 00:47:57.452
And also, all the output of AI, as you do serving,

00:47:57.452 --> 00:47:59.852
is going to be data about how your application is doing.

00:47:59.852 --> 00:48:02.612
It's got the same problems of quality and security.

00:48:02.612 --> 00:48:04.612
So we really need it to be unified.

00:48:04.612 --> 00:48:07.171
And then finally, we heard everyone

00:48:07.171 --> 00:48:11.411
asking for open access from any compute engine or client,

00:48:11.411 --> 00:48:15.011
because there are so many great solutions out there.

00:48:15.011 --> 00:48:16.411
They'll keep coming out.

00:48:16.411 --> 00:48:18.251
They'll be the next data processing engine,

00:48:18.251 --> 00:48:19.671
the next machine learning library.

00:48:19.671 --> 00:48:21.612
You want it to work with your data.

00:48:21.612 --> 00:48:25.452
So this is what we're building with Unity Catalog,

00:48:25.452 --> 00:48:27.891
especially with the open source launch today.

00:48:27.891 --> 00:48:29.771
So first of all, open connectivity.

00:48:29.771 --> 00:48:34.452
Unity Catalog and Databricks as a platform

00:48:34.452 --> 00:48:37.531
uniquely lets you connect data in other systems

00:48:37.531 --> 00:48:40.612
as well and process it together in a very efficient way

00:48:40.612 --> 00:48:42.612
through this feature we call Lakehouse Federation.

00:48:42.612 --> 00:48:44.651
So you can really connect all your data

00:48:44.651 --> 00:48:47.572
and give users a single place where you set security

00:48:47.572 --> 00:48:51.251
policies, you manage quality, and you make it available.

00:48:51.251 --> 00:48:55.572
It also is the only governance system in the industry,

00:48:55.572 --> 00:48:58.131
really, that's unified governance for data and AI.

00:48:58.131 --> 00:49:01.732
So since the beginning, since we launched this three years ago,

00:49:01.732 --> 00:49:04.732
we had support for tables, models, files.

00:49:04.732 --> 00:49:08.131
And we're adding new concepts as they come out

00:49:08.131 --> 00:49:09.832
in the AI world, like tools, which

00:49:09.832 --> 00:49:12.212
we talked about yesterday with the tool catalog

00:49:12.212 --> 00:49:14.171
concept for Gen AI agents.

00:49:14.171 --> 00:49:15.551
And for all these things, you can

00:49:15.551 --> 00:49:19.371
get these capabilities on top, ranging from access control

00:49:19.371 --> 00:49:22.612
to lineage to monitoring and discovery.

00:49:22.612 --> 00:49:25.251
And finally, one of the big things that

00:49:25.251 --> 00:49:28.692
is possible today through the open API and open source

00:49:28.692 --> 00:49:32.492
project we just launched is open access to all your tables

00:49:32.492 --> 00:49:34.952
through a wide range of applications.

00:49:34.952 --> 00:49:36.891
I'll talk more about that in a bit.

00:49:36.891 --> 00:49:40.332
But the cool thing here is, again, it's not just data

00:49:40.332 --> 00:49:43.452
systems like DocDB, but also a lot of the leading machine

00:49:43.452 --> 00:49:46.572
learning ones, like LangChain, can integrate with Unity

00:49:46.572 --> 00:49:48.131
Catalog.

00:49:43.124 --> 00:49:45.124
brainstorms about the upcoming sensibility design.

00:49:47.424 --> 00:49:49.424
So cloud cloud injection is a very

00:49:51.624 --> 00:49:53.624
soon powerful set of capabilities that

00:49:54.504 --> 00:49:56.504
high-tech phones and cell phones and

00:50:00.924 --> 00:50:02.924
technology can integrate with.

00:50:05.264 --> 00:50:07.444
It's been widely adopted and some of them are managing tens

00:50:07.444 --> 00:50:09.144
of petabytes of data like GM or have thousands of active users

00:50:09.144 --> 00:50:11.144
like Pepsi here.

00:50:12.904 --> 00:50:15.144
It's been widely adopted and some of them are managing tens of

00:50:15.144 --> 00:50:17.644
petabytes of data like GM or have thousands of active users

00:50:17.644 --> 00:50:19.644
like Pepsi here.

00:50:20.924 --> 00:50:22.924
So let me start with open connectivity.

00:50:24.203 --> 00:50:26.203
So I'm really excited today to announce

00:50:27.284 --> 00:50:29.784
GA of lake house federation, the ability to connect and manage

00:50:29.784 --> 00:50:31.784
external data sources in Unity.

00:50:34.064 --> 00:50:36.064
Thanks, everyone.

00:50:37.343 --> 00:50:39.264
So this is a feature that we launched last year, a year ago

00:50:39.264 --> 00:50:41.264
at summit.

00:50:43.023 --> 00:50:45.023
It's a new feature that we launched

00:50:46.604 --> 00:50:48.603
in the last year, it's called lake

00:50:49.884 --> 00:50:51.904
house federation, it's going to allow you to use the same

00:50:51.904 --> 00:50:54.963
governance rules on top and get the same experience managing

00:50:54.963 --> 00:50:57.344
quality, tracking lineage and so on as people work on them that

