01:05:18.044 --> 01:05:20.044
So as I said,

01:05:20.044 --> 01:05:22.044
Ali let me keep one thing to announce today

01:05:22.044 --> 01:05:24.044
which I'm really excited

01:05:24.044 --> 01:05:26.044
about. So what we just saw

01:05:26.044 --> 01:05:28.044
is you could set up a Catalog,

01:05:28.044 --> 01:05:30.044
it's open, it's got access control,

01:05:30.044 --> 01:05:32.044
monitoring, you can get to it

01:05:32.044 --> 01:05:34.044
from any engine, you can federate stuff

01:05:34.044 --> 01:05:36.044
into it. Are you done?

01:05:36.044 --> 01:05:38.044
As an engineer, you might say this is pretty good.

01:05:38.044 --> 01:05:40.044
What will happen, unfortunately, is

01:05:40.044 --> 01:05:42.044
someone will come in and ask

01:05:42.044 --> 01:05:44.044
a business question. For example,

01:05:44.044 --> 01:05:46.044
how is my ARR trending

01:05:46.044 --> 01:05:48.044
in EMEA? And to answer this

01:05:48.044 --> 01:05:50.044
kind of question, there's not enough

01:05:50.044 --> 01:05:52.044
information in just the Catalog,

01:05:52.044 --> 01:05:54.044
in just the table schemas and things like that.

01:05:54.044 --> 01:05:56.044
So you have to understand things

01:05:56.044 --> 01:05:58.044
like how is ARR defined?

01:05:58.044 --> 01:06:00.044
That's some kind of unique calculation

01:06:00.044 --> 01:06:02.044
for your business.

01:06:02.044 --> 01:06:04.044
Maybe there are many tables that mention ARR.

01:06:04.044 --> 01:06:06.044
Which one actually is the right

01:06:06.044 --> 01:06:08.044
one to use to get this information?

01:06:08.044 --> 01:06:10.044
How is EMEA defined? Which countries

01:06:10.044 --> 01:06:12.044
are really part of it? And so on.

01:06:12.044 --> 01:06:14.044
And so the question is, how do you

01:06:14.044 --> 01:06:16.044
bridge this gap? So this is

01:06:16.044 --> 01:06:18.044
something that is typically done

01:06:18.044 --> 01:06:20.044
in some kind of metrics layer

01:06:20.044 --> 01:06:22.044
and we're really excited to announce

01:06:22.044 --> 01:06:24.044
that we're adding first class support

01:06:24.044 --> 01:06:26.044
for metrics as a concept

01:06:26.044 --> 01:06:28.044
in Unity Catalog.

01:06:28.044 --> 01:06:30.044
So, yeah.

01:06:30.044 --> 01:06:32.044
Applause

01:06:32.044 --> 01:06:34.044
Yeah, thanks.

01:06:34.044 --> 01:06:36.044
So this is something

01:06:36.044 --> 01:06:38.044
we'll be

01:06:38.044 --> 01:06:40.044
rolling out

01:06:40.044 --> 01:06:42.044
later this year.

01:06:42.044 --> 01:06:44.044
So Unity Catalog

01:06:44.044 --> 01:06:46.044
metrics. So the

01:06:46.044 --> 01:06:48.044
idea here is that you can define metrics

01:06:48.044 --> 01:06:50.044
inside Unity Catalog

01:06:50.044 --> 01:06:52.044
and manage them together with all

01:06:52.044 --> 01:06:54.044
the other assets. So you can set

01:06:54.044 --> 01:06:56.044
governance rules on them, you can find them

01:06:56.044 --> 01:06:58.044
in search, you can get audit events,

01:06:58.044 --> 01:07:00.044
you can get lineage for them

01:07:00.044 --> 01:07:02.044
and so on. And like the

01:07:02.044 --> 01:07:04.044
other parts of Unity, we're taking

01:07:04.044 --> 01:07:06.044
an open approach to this. We want

01:07:06.044 --> 01:07:08.044
you to be able to use the metrics in

01:07:08.044 --> 01:07:10.044
any downstream tool.

01:07:10.044 --> 01:07:12.044
So we're going to expose them to multiple

01:07:12.044 --> 01:07:14.044
BI tools. So you can pick the BI

01:07:14.044 --> 01:07:16.044
tool of your choice. We'll of course

01:07:16.044 --> 01:07:18.044
integrate them with AIBI.

01:07:18.044 --> 01:07:20.044
One of the things we're excited about is we're designing

01:07:20.044 --> 01:07:22.044
metrics from the beginning to be AI

01:07:22.044 --> 01:07:24.044
friendly so that AIBI

01:07:24.044 --> 01:07:26.044
and similar tools can really

01:07:26.044 --> 01:07:28.044
understand how to use these

01:07:28.044 --> 01:07:30.044
and give you great results.

01:07:30.044 --> 01:07:32.044
And you'll be able to just use them

01:07:32.044 --> 01:07:34.044
through SQL, through

01:07:34.044 --> 01:07:36.044
table functions that you can compute on.

01:07:36.044 --> 01:07:38.044
And we are also partnering

01:07:38.044 --> 01:07:40.044
with DBT, Kube, and AtSkill

01:07:40.044 --> 01:07:42.044
as external metrics provider

01:07:42.044 --> 01:07:44.044
to make it easy to bring in

01:07:44.044 --> 01:07:46.044
and govern and manage metrics from those

01:07:46.044 --> 01:07:48.044
inside Unity. So

01:07:48.044 --> 01:07:50.044
with all of this stuff in action, I'd like

01:07:50.044 --> 01:07:52.044
to invite Zeeshan to the stage again for

01:07:52.044 --> 01:07:54.044
a quick demo of metrics.

