01:10:44.044 --> 01:10:46.044
Very nice to see those.

01:10:46.044 --> 01:10:48.044
All right. So, the

01:10:48.044 --> 01:10:50.044
final portion of the talk I want to talk about,

01:10:50.044 --> 01:10:52.044
I want to talk about what we're doing

01:10:52.044 --> 01:10:54.044
in sharing and cross-org collaboration.

01:10:54.044 --> 01:10:56.044
Depending

01:10:56.044 --> 01:10:58.044
what industry you're in, you've probably

01:10:58.044 --> 01:11:00.044
seen that data sharing and

01:11:00.044 --> 01:11:02.044
collaboration between companies,

01:11:02.044 --> 01:11:04.044
between organizations, is

01:11:04.044 --> 01:11:06.044
becoming a really important part of the

01:11:06.044 --> 01:11:08.044
modern data space. It can help

01:11:08.044 --> 01:11:10.044
providers and suppliers

01:11:10.044 --> 01:11:12.044
coordinate better. It can help

01:11:12.044 --> 01:11:14.044
streamline a lot of

01:11:14.044 --> 01:11:16.044
business processes. Just yesterday, I met a

01:11:16.044 --> 01:11:18.044
customer who thought that they could

01:11:18.044 --> 01:11:20.044
speed up, basically, launching

01:11:20.044 --> 01:11:22.044
new drugs by a factor of two

01:11:22.044 --> 01:11:24.044
by implementing these

01:11:24.044 --> 01:11:26.044
kind of technologies.

01:11:26.044 --> 01:11:28.044
So, really powerful

01:11:28.044 --> 01:11:30.044
way for many industries

01:11:30.044 --> 01:11:32.044
to move forward. And we started

01:11:32.044 --> 01:11:34.044
looking at this area about three

01:11:34.044 --> 01:11:36.044
years ago. We wanted to provide great support

01:11:36.044 --> 01:11:38.044
for it. And we started by talking

01:11:38.044 --> 01:11:40.044
to a lot of data providers who collaborate.

01:11:40.044 --> 01:11:42.044
And what they told us

01:11:42.044 --> 01:11:44.044
was that many of

01:11:44.044 --> 01:11:46.044
the data platforms out there

01:11:46.044 --> 01:11:48.044
support some kind of sharing between different

01:11:48.044 --> 01:11:50.044
instances, but it's always closed.

01:11:50.044 --> 01:11:52.044
You can only share within that same

01:11:52.044 --> 01:11:54.044
data platform, within that

01:11:54.044 --> 01:11:56.044
customers of that data warehouse or whatever.

01:11:56.044 --> 01:11:58.044
And as a provider, or as any

01:11:58.044 --> 01:12:00.044
company that wants to collaborate with a lot of

01:12:00.044 --> 01:12:02.044
partners, this is very restrictive.

01:12:02.044 --> 01:12:04.044
So, Empirity, for example, who's

01:12:04.044 --> 01:12:06.044
a CDP,

01:12:06.044 --> 01:12:08.044
said that they would prefer to invest

01:12:08.044 --> 01:12:10.044
in open solutions that

01:12:10.044 --> 01:12:12.044
let them set up data

01:12:12.044 --> 01:12:14.044
collaboration once and then

01:12:14.044 --> 01:12:16.044
be able to reach anyone, regardless of what

01:12:16.044 --> 01:12:18.044
platform they're computing on.

01:12:18.044 --> 01:12:20.044
So, that's the approach that we've taken

01:12:20.044 --> 01:12:22.044
with all our sharing and collaboration

01:12:22.044 --> 01:12:24.044
infrastructure by

01:12:24.044 --> 01:12:26.044
creating an open collaboration ecosystem

01:12:26.044 --> 01:12:28.044
based on open standards.

01:12:28.044 --> 01:12:30.044
And the core of that is delta

01:12:30.044 --> 01:12:32.044
sharing, a feature of

01:12:32.044 --> 01:12:34.044
Delta Lake that allows you to securely

01:12:34.044 --> 01:12:36.044
share tables

01:12:36.044 --> 01:12:38.044
across clouds and across data platforms.

01:12:38.044 --> 01:12:40.044
And then we've built on that with Databricks

01:12:40.044 --> 01:12:42.044
Marketplace and Databricks Clean Homes.

01:12:42.044 --> 01:12:44.044
So, if you're not familiar with

01:12:44.044 --> 01:12:46.044
delta sharing, basically

01:12:46.044 --> 01:12:48.044
this is a core part of the

01:12:48.044 --> 01:12:50.044
Delta Lake project, where if you

01:12:50.044 --> 01:12:52.044
have a table and

01:12:52.044 --> 01:12:54.044
increasingly other kinds of assets as well,

01:12:54.044 --> 01:12:56.044
you can run this server

01:12:56.044 --> 01:12:58.044
that has an open protocol

01:12:58.044 --> 01:13:00.044
and serve out just parts of your table

01:13:00.044 --> 01:13:02.044
to other parties that are

01:13:02.044 --> 01:13:04.044
authorized to access them.

01:13:04.044 --> 01:13:06.044
And because the protocol is open,

01:13:06.044 --> 01:13:08.044
it's a very simple one based on

01:13:08.044 --> 01:13:10.044
Parquet files

01:13:10.044 --> 01:13:12.044
that they're given access to,

01:13:12.044 --> 01:13:14.044
it's really easy to implement

01:13:14.044 --> 01:13:16.044
a lot of consumers. So, of course, you can

01:13:16.044 --> 01:13:18.044
use Databricks to access these, but you can also

01:13:18.044 --> 01:13:20.044
just use Pandas, Apache Spark,

01:13:20.044 --> 01:13:22.044
even BI products like

01:13:22.044 --> 01:13:24.044
Tableau and Power BI

01:13:24.044 --> 01:13:26.044
are letting you load data right into

01:13:26.044 --> 01:13:28.044
there. And it makes a lot of sense.

01:13:28.044 --> 01:13:30.044
If you're a data provider, you want to publish

01:13:30.044 --> 01:13:32.044
something, why should the other party

01:13:32.044 --> 01:13:34.044
even need to install a data

01:13:34.044 --> 01:13:36.044
warehouse in the first place? Why not deliver that

01:13:36.044 --> 01:13:38.044
data, say, straight to Tableau or straight to

01:13:38.044 --> 01:13:40.044
Excel or something like that?

01:14:10.169 --> 01:14:16.969
40% of those recipients are not on Databricks. So this idea of cross-platform collaboration

01:14:17.528 --> 01:14:23.769
is real and our customers are able to deliver data and to have real-time data exchange with

01:14:23.769 --> 01:14:27.048
anyone regardless of what data platform they're using.

01:14:27.048 --> 01:14:29.848
So super excited about the growth of that this year.

01:14:25.127 --> 01:14:27.127
Day 3

01:14:28.207 --> 01:14:30.207
.

01:14:37.607 --> 01:14:39.607
We are continuing to expand Delta sharing

01:14:40.887 --> 01:14:42.967
and one exciting announcement is we're hooking together two of

01:14:42.967 --> 01:14:44.967
the best features

01:14:46.047 --> 01:14:48.067
of the platform, Lakehouse federation and sharing to let

01:14:48.067 --> 01:14:52.367
you share data automatically from other data sources as well.

01:14:52.367 --> 01:14:55.047
So we talk to a lot of companies who have some data in a data

01:14:55.266 --> 01:14:57.367
warehouse and they have some data in a data warehouse and

01:14:57.367 --> 01:14:59.867
they want to share it to the other end of the platform, they

01:14:59.867 --> 01:15:03.246
want to share it to the other end of the platform, but they

01:15:03.246 --> 01:15:05.307
want to collaborate. And since we built this federation

01:15:05.307 --> 01:15:09.707
technology that can efficiently query this data, push down

01:15:09.707 --> 01:15:13.726
filters, get it out and deliver it, we are just connecting that

01:15:13.726 --> 01:15:16.687
to Delta sharing to let you seamlessly do this. So now you

01:15:16.687 --> 01:15:20.187
can really share data from, you know, any data warehouse, any

01:15:20.187 --> 01:15:22.807
database with any app that understands the Delta sharing

01:15:23.187 --> 01:15:25.726
capability that we provide and you can do that from the

01:15:25.726 --> 01:15:28.127
own end. Thank you very much, this is really exciting to say

01:15:28.127 --> 01:15:30.726
thank you for you being the White papers for this.

01:15:36.826 --> 01:15:40.226
So one of the things that builds on Delta sharing is data

01:15:40.226 --> 01:15:42.226
marketplace.

01:15:44.347 --> 01:15:46.347
This is something we launched about two years ago.

01:15:49.826 --> 01:15:52.027
And it's also been going extremely

01:15:52.686 --> 01:15:54.686
well and we are very excited about it.

01:15:55.906 --> 01:15:58.167
We are the first data marketplaces anywhere in the

01:15:58.167 --> 01:16:00.167
cloud on any platform.

01:16:01.466 --> 01:16:03.466
So it's continuing to go.

01:16:04.546 --> 01:16:06.947
Our team has been adding a whole bunch of new functionality

01:16:06.947 --> 01:16:10.646
there that providers are asking for like private exchanges,

01:16:10.646 --> 01:16:14.686
sharing of non-data assets like models and volumes, usage

01:16:14.686 --> 01:16:16.686
analytics and even support for non-database clients.

01:16:18.987 --> 01:16:20.506
If you put data in there, you can reach these other platforms

01:16:20.506 --> 01:16:22.506
and it's a lot of fun.

01:16:23.787 --> 01:16:25.787
So we are very excited about that.

01:16:26.866 --> 01:16:28.866
And we are also very excited to

01:16:29.947 --> 01:16:32.466
welcome 12 new partners to this, to the sharing and marketplace

01:16:32.466 --> 01:16:36.447
ecosystems. Some of these announcements went out last

01:16:36.447 --> 01:16:41.386
week, but anywhere from Axiom, Amperity, Atlassian, industry

01:16:41.386 --> 01:16:44.386
leaders in many different domains are now connecting to

01:16:44.386 --> 01:16:49.427
this ecosystems and making data available to users on Databricks

01:16:49.427 --> 01:16:51.427
and we are very excited to see how this will continue to go.

01:16:53.746 --> 01:16:55.746
And we are also very excited to see

01:16:56.826 --> 01:16:58.826
how this will continue to grow in the ecosystem of partners.

01:17:00.106 --> 01:17:02.106
So thanks to all of them who are participating in this.

01:17:02.166 --> 01:17:04.166
Great.

01:17:05.246 --> 01:17:07.166
So, yeah, really excited to see how this will continue to go in

01:17:07.166 --> 01:17:09.166
the future.

01:17:10.466 --> 01:17:12.466
The final thing I want to talk about is

01:17:13.546 --> 01:17:15.627
that we are soon launching public preview of Databricks

01:17:15.627 --> 01:17:17.627
cleanrooms.

01:17:19.707 --> 01:17:21.707
So what is a cleanroom?

01:17:23.987 --> 01:17:25.987
It's a place where you can have a

01:17:27.067 --> 01:17:29.067
database, a database of some tables, some code, some

01:17:29.067 --> 01:17:31.067
unstructured data, some AI models, any kind of asset you

01:17:31.067 --> 01:17:33.306
can have on the Databricks platform and you can agree on a

01:17:33.306 --> 01:17:35.306
computation with someone else that you run and then send the

01:17:37.546 --> 01:17:39.906
results to just one recipient. So, for example, it could be as

01:17:39.906 --> 01:17:41.906
simple as you each have some tables and you want to figure

01:17:41.906 --> 01:17:44.587
